Next step: Push schema to NeonDB! 🚀- ✅ **Gamification** via Badge system- ✅ **Social features** via Post model- ✅ **Scalable** for 100+ concurrent users- ✅ **Next-Auth v5** integration- ✅ **Optimized indexes** for real-time queries- ✅ **pgvector** for AI embeddings (Gemini)- ✅ **9 models** covering all features## Summary---```psql $DATABASE_URL < backup.sql```bash**Restore:**```pg_dump $DATABASE_URL > backup.sql```bash**Manual export:**NeonDB has automatic backups (point-in-time recovery).## Backup & Recovery---Run: `pnpm db:seed````  .finally(() => prisma.$disconnect());  .catch(console.error)main()}  });    ]      // ... more badges      },        points: 10        rarity: 'common',        criteria: { type: 'total_pomodoros', threshold: 1 },        category: 'FOCUS',        icon: '🎯',        description: 'Complete your first Pomodoro',        name: 'First Focus',      {    data: [  await prisma.badge.createMany({  // Create badgesasync function main() {const prisma = new PrismaClient();import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';```typescriptCreate `apps/api/prisma/seed.ts` for demo data:## Data Seeding (Optional)---```});  }    task: { select: { title: true } }    user: { select: { name: true, avatar: true } },  include: {  },    startedAt: { gte: new Date(Date.now() - 30 * 60 * 1000) } // Last 30 min    status: 'IN_PROGRESS',  where: {const focusingUsers = await prisma.focusSession.findMany({```typescript### 4. Who's Focusing Right Now?````;  LIMIT 5  ORDER BY embedding <=> ${queryEmbedding}::vector  WHERE userId = ${userId}  FROM tasks  SELECT id, title, 1 - (embedding <=> ${queryEmbedding}::vector) as similarityconst similarTasks = await prisma.$queryRaw`// Then, find similar tasks using vector searchconst queryEmbedding = await getEmbedding("write blog post");// First, get embedding from Gemini for user's query```typescript### 3. Find Similar Tasks (AI RAG)```});  }    images: true    task: { select: { title: true, status: true } },    user: { select: { name: true, avatar: true } },  include: {  take: 20,  orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },  where: { isPublic: true },const feed = await prisma.post.findMany({```typescript### 2. Get Public Feed (World)```});  }    user: { select: { name: true, avatar: true } }  include: {  take: 10,  orderBy: { totalFocusTime: 'desc' },  where: { date: new Date('2026-02-05') },const leaderboard = await prisma.dailyStats.findMany({```typescript### 1. Get Daily Leaderboard## Sample Queries---```prisma migrate deploy# Deploy migrationpnpm db:migrate# Create migration```bash### Production (Later)```pnpm db:studio# 3. Verify in Prisma Studiopnpm db:push# 2. Push schema to NeonDB (dev only)pnpm db:generate# 1. Generate Prisma Clientcd apps/api```bash### Initial Setup (Day 1)## Migration Strategy---     ```     CREATE INDEX ON tasks USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops);     ```sql   - Create HNSW index on `embedding` column:5. **Vector Search Optimization:**   - Leaderboard: Offset-based OK (small dataset, resets daily)   - Feed: Cursor-based (use `createdAt + id`)4. **Pagination:**   - Invalidate on new focus session   - Cache "who's online" for 30 seconds   - Cache leaderboard for 5 minutes3. **Caching (Redis):**   - Write to primary, read from replica   - Use NeonDB read replicas for leaderboard queries2. **Read Replicas:**   - Set `connection_limit` in DATABASE_URL   - NeonDB has built-in pooling1. **Connection Pooling:**### For High User Count (100+ concurrent users)## Scaling Considerations---   Optimizes: `WHERE status = 'IN_PROGRESS' ORDER BY startedAt DESC`   ```   @@index([status, startedAt])   ```prisma4. **Real-time Focus** (Who's Online):   Optimizes: `WHERE userId = ? AND status = 'TODAY'`   ```   @@index([userId, status])   ```prisma3. **User's Tasks** (Kanban):   Optimizes: `WHERE date = ? ORDER BY totalFocusTime DESC LIMIT 10`   ```   @@index([date, totalFocusTime])   ```prisma2. **Leaderboard** (Daily Stats):   Optimizes: `WHERE isPublic = true ORDER BY createdAt DESC`   ```   @@index([isPublic, createdAt])   ```prisma1. **Feed Query** (Public Posts):### Composite Indexes (Most Important)## Indexes & Performance---- Email verification tokens (if email/password added later)**VerificationToken:**- `sessionToken`, `expires`, `userId`- Active user sessions**Session:**- `provider: "google"`, `providerAccountId`, `access_token`, etc.- Stores OAuth provider data (Google)**Account:**These are **standard Next-Auth v5 tables**. Automatically managed by `@auth/prisma-adapter`.### Account, Session, VerificationToken## Next-Auth Tables---**UserBadge:** Junction table, links users to their unlocked badges```}  "rarity": "epic"  "category": "MILESTONE",  "criteria": { "type": "total_pomodoros", "threshold": 100 },  "name": "Century Club",{}  "rarity": "rare"  "category": "CONSISTENCY",  "criteria": { "type": "streak_days", "threshold": 7 },  "name": "Week Warrior",{}  "rarity": "common"  "category": "FOCUS",  "criteria": { "type": "total_pomodoros", "threshold": 1 },  "name": "First Focus",{```json**Example Badges:**- `points`: Score value- `rarity`: common | rare | epic | legendary- `criteria`: JSON rules for unlocking- `category`: FOCUS | CONSISTENCY | PRODUCTIVITY | SOCIAL | MILESTONE- `icon`: Emoji (🔥, 💪, 🏆)- `description`: What it's for- `name`: "First Focus", "Week Warrior", "Century Club"**Badge Model:****Purpose:** Achievement system to motivate users### 8. Badge & UserBadge (Gamification)---4. **Productivity Tip**: Daily tips based on stats3. **Motivation**: "Give me a motivational quote"2. **Task Breakdown**: "Break this big task into subtasks"1. **Task Suggestions**: Based on user's history (RAG with embeddings)**Use Cases:**- `user`: Who made the request**Relations:**- `tokensUsed`: For cost tracking- `model`: Track which Gemini model used (e.g., "gemini-1.5-flash")- `wasHelpful`: User feedback (thumbs up/down)- `aiResponse`: Gemini's output- `context`: JSON with additional data (recent tasks, stats, etc.)- `userPrompt`: User's input (optional)- `type`: TASK_SUGGESTION | TASK_BREAKDOWN | MOTIVATION | PRODUCTIVITY_TIP**Key Fields:****Purpose:** Log all AI interactions for analytics and feedback### 7. AIInteraction (Gemini Chat History)---**Reset:** Leaderboard resets at midnight (UTC or user's timezone)```LIMIT 10ORDER BY dailyStats.totalFocusTime DESCWHERE dailyStats.date = '2026-02-05'JOIN user ON dailyStats.userId = user.idFROM dailyStatsSELECT user.name, dailyStats.totalFocusTime```sql**Leaderboard Logic:**- `(date, totalFocusTime DESC)` - **Leaderboard query** (very fast!)- `(userId, date)` - Unique constraint, one record per user per day**Indexes:**- `user`: Stats owner**Relations:**- `completedTasks`: Tasks moved to DONE- `completedPomodoros`: Count of 25-min sessions- `totalFocusTime`: Seconds focused that day- `date`: The day (Date only, no time)**Key Fields:****Purpose:** Aggregate daily metrics for leaderboard### 6. DailyStats (Leaderboard Data)---- Status changes to COMPLETED when timer ends- All online users see their avatar + countdown timer- WebSocket broadcasts when user starts focus**Real-time Use:**- `startedAt` - Real-time "who's focusing now" query- `(userId, status)` - Find active sessions- `(userId, startedAt)` - User's history**Indexes:**- `task`: What they worked on (optional - can focus without task)- `user`: Who focused**Relations:**- `breakDuration`: Optional break time after session- `status`: IN_PROGRESS | COMPLETED | INTERRUPTED- `plannedDuration`: Usually 1500s (25 min)- `duration`: Actual seconds focused- `startedAt`, `endedAt`: Session timestamps**Key Fields:****Purpose:** Track every focus session (Pomodoro timer)### 5. FocusSession (Pomodoro Tracking)---- Cloudinary: Free 25GB, more features- Uploadthing: Free 2GB, easy Next.js integration**Storage:** Images uploaded to **Uploadthing** (recommended) or Cloudinary- `post`: Parent post**Relations:**- `width`, `height`, `size`, `format`: Metadata for optimization- `url`: Cloudinary or Uploadthing URL**Key Fields:****Purpose:** Store multiple images per post### 4. PostImage (Image Attachments)---User completes a task → Creates a Post with description + images → Everyone in "World" sees it**Use Case:**- `createdAt` - Time-based sorting- `userId` - User's post history- `(isPublic, createdAt DESC)` - Optimized for feed query**Indexes:**- `images[]`: Attached photos (via Uploadthing/Cloudinary)- `task`: Optional - the task being shared- `user`: Author**Relations:**- `taskId`: Optional link to the original task (can be null for general posts)- `viewCount`, `likeCount`: Engagement metrics- `isPublic`: Always `true` (all posts are public in "World")- `content`: User's description/story about the task (required, Text)**Key Fields:****Purpose:** Share completed tasks with community ("World" feed)### 3. Post (Public Social Sharing)---**Privacy:** Tasks are **private by default**. Only visible to owner unless shared via Post.- `status` - Global stats queries- `(userId, isArchived)` - Hide archived tasks- `(userId, status)` - Fetch tasks by column**Indexes:**- `focusSessions[]`: Pomodoro sessions done on this task- `posts[]`: If user shares this task publicly- `user`: Owner of the task**Relations:**- `embedding`: Vector(768) for AI similarity search (Gemini embeddings)- `dueDate`: Optional deadline- `tags[]`: Array of labels (e.g., ["work", "urgent"])- `completedPomodoros`: How many actually done- `estimatedPomodoros`: How many 25-min sessions planned- `priority`: LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH | URGENT- `status`: BACKLOG | TODAY | DONE (Kanban columns)- `title`, `description`: Task content**Key Fields:****Purpose:** User's personal task list (Kanban board)### 2. Task (Private Todo Management)---- `email` - Fast login lookup**Indexes:**- `dailyStats[]`: Daily aggregate data- `userBadges[]`: Unlocked achievements- `aiInteractions[]`: AI chat history- `focusSessions[]`: Pomodoro history- `posts[]`: User's public shares- `tasks[]`: User's private tasks**Relations:**- `totalFocusTime`, `currentStreak`, `longestStreak`: Gamification stats- `timezone`: For accurate Pomodoro timing- `name`, `avatar`, `bio`: Profile information- `email`: For Google OAuth login- `id` (cuid): Unique identifier**Key Fields:****Purpose:** Store user accounts, profile info, and stats### 1. User (Authentication & Profile)## Core Models---```└─────────────┘│  PostImage  │┌─────────────┐      ▼      │ 1:N      │└─────────────┘│    Post     │────┘┌─────────────┐    │      ▼            │      │ 1:N        │      │            │└─────────────┘    ││    Task     │    │┌─────────────┐    │      ▼            │      │ 1:N        │      │            │└─────────────┘    ││    User     │◄───┐┌─────────────┐```## Entity Relationship Diagram---Schema location: [`apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma`](../apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma)ORM: **Prisma**Database: **PostgreSQL** (NeonDB with pgvector extension)## OverviewGEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...

